definition.value: An organosulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfate group of 1-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl-(1->4)-beta-D-glucosyl)-N-acylsphingosine; major species at pH 7.3.

A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is pentacosane in which a hydrogen attached to one of the terminal carbons is replaced by a hydroxy group. It has been identified in the roots of Rhodiola imbricata.
A galactosylglycerolipid with an alkyl group at the sn-1 position, an acyl group at the sn-2 position and a beta-D-galactosyl residue at the sn-3 position.
An organosulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfate group of any 1-alkyl-2-acyl-3-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)-sn-glycerol; major species at pH 7.3.
An organosulfate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the sulfate group of any 1,2-diacyl-3-(3-O-sulfo-beta-D-galactosyl)glycerol; major species at pH 7.3.

A member of the class of aminopyrimidines that is 2,6-diamino-5-chloropyrimidine in which the amino groups at positions 2 and 6 are respectively carrying 2-methoxy-4-(piperidin-4-yl)-5-methylphenyl and 2-(isopropylsulfonyl)phenyl substituents. Used for the treatment of ALK-positive metastatic non-small cell lung cancer.

A substance used in a thermodynamic heat pump cycle or refrigeration cycle that undergoes a phase change from a gas to a liquid and back. Refrigerants are used in air-conditioning systems and freezers or refrigerators and are assigned a "R" number (by ASHRAE - formerly the American Society of Heating, Refrigerating and Air Conditioning Engineers), which is determined systematically according to their molecular structure.

A single-stranded DNA oligonucleotide comprised of nine deoxyadenosine, eight thymidine, two deoxycytidine and two deoxyguanosine residues connected by 3'->5' phosphodiester linkages in the sequence A-A-A-A-A-T-C-C-T-T-T-T-T-G-G-A-T-T-A-A-A. Synthetic model oligodeoxyribonucleotide ligand.

A polyanionic polymer obtained by deprotonation of the diphosphate and carboxy groups of [GlcNAc-(1->4)-Mur2Ac(oyl-L-Ala-gamma-D-Glu-L-Lys-D-Ala-D-Ala)]n-diphospho-ditrans,polycis-undecaprenol; major species at pH 7.3.
A carbohydrate acid derivative dianion that is the conjugate base of the ganglioside GD3 arising from deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups; major species at pH 7.3.
An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GT3; major species at pH 7.3.
A long-chain fatty aldehyde resulting from the formal oxidation of the hydroxy group of hexacosan-1-ol. It is a minor component of barley leaf wax.
A thioribose consisting of D-ribofuranose in which the hydroxy group at position 3 is replaced by a methylthio group.
A long-chain fatty aldehyde resulting from the formal oxidation of the hydroxy group of octacosan-1-ol.
A 3'-end ribonucleotide(1-) residue obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH group of 3'-end AMP residue; major species at pH 7.3.

A monounsaturated fatty acid that is nonadecanoic acid that has been dehydrogenated to introduce a double bond with Z configuration between the carbons at positions 9 and 10. It has been isolated from the spores of reishi mushroom, Ganoderma lucidum, and found to inhibit tumour cell proliferation and induce apoptosis of HL-60 cells.
Any EC 3.1.1.* (carboxylic ester hydrolase) inhibitor that inhibits the action of carboxylesterase (EC 3.1.1.1 ).
An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GD1a; major species at pH 7.3.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as acetyl.
An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GT1a; major species at pH 7.3.
A heptadecenoic acid in which the double bond is located at the 8-9 position and has Z configuration.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as malonyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as acetoacetyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxybutanoyl.
An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GT1b; major species at pH 7.3.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E)-butenoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as butanoyl.
An anionic ganglioside obtained by deprotonation of the neuraminosyl carboxy groups of ganglioside GQ1b; major species at pH 7.3.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 3-oxohexanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxyhexanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E)-hexenoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as hexanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 3-oxooctanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxyoctanoyl.
An O-(S-(2E)-enoylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)-L-serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E)-octenoyl; major species at pH 7.3.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as octanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 3-oxodecanoyl.
An alkene that is pentacosane which has been dehydrogenated to introduce a double bond at the 1-2 position.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxyoctanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E)-decenoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as decanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 3-oxodecanoyl.

A 2-aminopyrimidin-4(1H)-one derivative bearing a 1,3-benzodioxol-5-ylmethyl group at the 5-position and with a 4-(5-methyl-(1H)imidazol-4-yl)-3-thiabutyl substituent attached to the 2-amino group. It is a specific histamine H2-receptor antagonist.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxydodecanoyl.
An alkene that is nonacosane which has been dehydrogenated to introduce a double bond at the 1-2 position.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E)-dodecenoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as 3-oxotetradecanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (3R)-hydroxytetradecanoyl.
An O-(S-acylpantetheine-4'-phosphoryl)serine(1-) residue in which the S-acyl group is specified as (2E)-tetradecenoyl.
